.TH "ti_bandgap_power" 9 "ti_bandgap_power" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_bandgap_power \- controls the power state of a bandgap device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ti_bandgap_power
.BI "(struct ti_bandgap *bgp "  ","
.BI "bool on "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bgp" 12
pointer to ti_bandgap structure
.IP "on" 12
desired power state (1 - on, 0 - off)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used to power on/off a bandgap device instance. Only used on those
that features tempsoff bit.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -ENOTSUPP if tempsoff is not supported.
